TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION:
This source qualifier joins the TAPC_CLAIM_XMD table, which contains all the XMD APC claims being processed for the quarter, to the GDX RCIT_BASE_CLM_APC table, which is all the claims for the quarter.
The join is taking place in order to get ONLY the XMD APC claims being processed for this quarter, AND to get the MED-D amount fields. The output is for Mark Walkers group.
NOTE: The TAPC_CLAIM_XMD table is a working table, so it only stores 1 quarters worth of data at a time.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: SQ_XMD_APC_Claims

This table should only hold 6 quarters at a time. The Informatica process built to insert rows into it (runs with APC Process) should clean up the oldest quarter just prior to inserting a new. Installed on 3/17/2011 with the Med-D Phase 2 project.

It puts out the MIN/MAX Quarter period and Monthly periods, along with their associated Start and End dates, based on what values you pass in. Since it builds a Parameter file for use in another session, you also need to pass in the Folder, Workflow, and the Worklet or Session that will be using the new Parameter file.
